-- Swedish FSA appoints Martin Noreus deputy chief
-- 
-- Mon Feb 03, 2014 09:41AM EST
-- None



STOCKHOLM, Feb 3 (Reuters) - Sweden's Financial Services Authority has appointed Martin Noreus to the newly created position of deputy general director, putting him in charge of financial markets, banking and insurance, it said on Monday.

Noreus previously oversaw insurance groups, mutual funds and pension funds at the FSA.